The paper deals with the analysis of channel correlation in multiuser multiple-input multiple-output (MU-MIMO) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of channel correlation on system performance, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). The use of physical models to capture variations in the power angular spectra across multiple terminals suggests a focus on multimedia systems (cs.MM) and mobile computing (cs.MA).
